      "text": [
        ": حُمِمْتُ بِالْمَدِينَةِ يَوْماً فِي شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ فَبَعَثَ إِلَيَّ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ بِقَصْعَةٍ فِيهَا خَلٌّ وَ زَيْتٌ وَ قَالَ لِي «أَفْطِرْ وَ صَلِّ وَ أَنْتَ قَاعِدٌ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1942 - Jamil ibn Darraj narrated from Al-Walid ibn Sabih, who said:\n\"I became feverish one day in Medina during the Month of Ramadan. Abu Abdullah (as) sent me a dish containing vinegar and oil and said to me:\n'Break your fast and pray while sitting.'\""
        ]
      }
